==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*xudian-'', from Indo-European ''*kewdh-'' ‘conceal’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[heda|hēda]], Middle Dutch [[hüden]].  The IE root is also the source of Welsh [[cudd]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hy:dan/

===Verb===
'''hȳdan''' (class 1 weak)
# ''(transitive)'' to [[hide]] or [[conceal]], to [[hoard]]
# ''(intransitive)'' to [[hide]]

